components.name: Upload
components.description: The Upload component enables users to easily select and transfer files from their device to a server. It supports multiple file formats, offers drag-and-drop functionality, and provides visual feedback during the upload process, ensuring a seamless and efficient user experience.

customRequest.description: Allows overriding the default upload behavior with a custom implementation for handling file uploads.

isImageUrl.description: Supplies a custom function to determine whether a file should be treated as an image for preview purposes.

itemRender.description: Allows customization of how each uploaded file item is displayed in the list through a custom render function.

listType.description: Determines how the list of uploaded files is displayed, offering options like text, picture, or picture-card views.

maxCount.description: Limits the total number of files that can be uploaded through the component at any given time.

onChange.description: Fires whenever the file list changes, providing information about the current state of all files being uploaded.

components.description: The Loader component visually indicates that content is loading, enhancing user experience. It typically features animated graphics or spinners, signaling to users that their request is being processed. This component is essential for maintaining engagement during wait times in applications and websites.

components.description: The List component is a versatile UI element that displays a collection of items in a structured format. components.description: The InputWrapper component provides a flexible container for input elements, enhancing layout and styling. components.name: TextField
components.description: The TextField component is a versatile input element designed for user text entry. showOptionalText.description: show optional text along with label

onClick.description: Function called when button is clicked

components.name: Badge
components.description: The Badge component is a versatile UI element that displays a small, informative label, often used to convey status, notifications, or counts. It enhances user experience by providing quick visual cues, making it ideal for alerts, messages, or highlighting important information in applications.

children.description: Content to be wrapped by the badge, usually an icon or other element that needs a notification indicator

className.description: Additional CSS class names to apply for custom styling

color.description: Sets the badge's color theme from predefined options like red, blue, green, amber, or gray

tonal.description: When true, applies a lighter tonal variant of the badge color for a more subtle appearance

value.description: Numeric value displayed inside the badge, typically used to show counts or notifications

components.name: Avatar
components.description: The Avatar component displays a user's profile picture or initials, serving as a visual representation in user interfaces. It enhances personalization and identity recognition, often used in social media, messaging apps, and online platforms to foster engagement and connection among users.

crossOrigin.description: CORS setting for loading avatar image

draggable.description: Whether the avatar image is draggable

gap.description: Space between left/right edge and letters in avatar

icon.description: Custom icon component to display in avatar

onError.description: Handler for when avatar image fails to load

shape.description: Shape of avatar - circle or square

size.description: Size of avatar in pixels or preset

srcSet.description: Responsive image sources for different screen sizes

components.name: Alert
components.description: The Alert component is a notification tool that conveys important messages to users. It features customizable styles, icons, and actions, allowing for clear communication of success, error, warning, or informational alerts. Ideal for enhancing user experience by providing timely feedback and guidance.

buttonElement.description: Custom React element to override the default action button implementation

buttonLabel.description: Text displayed in the default action button when buttonElement is not provided

buttonType.description: Sets the action button's appearance as either an inline text link or full-width block

closable.description: Enables a close button that allows users to dismiss the alert

message.description: The main content to display in the alert, either as text or React element

onClickButton.description: Callback function executed when the action button is clicked

onClose.description: Callback function triggered when the alert is dismissed via the close button

showIcon.description: Controls the visibility of the status icon that appears at the start of the alert

type.description: Determines the alert's visual style and semantic meaning (success, warning, error, or info)

components.name: Accordion
components.description: The Accordion component is a collapsible UI element that organizes content into expandable sections. Users can click on headers to reveal or hide associated content, enhancing navigation and saving space. Ideal for FAQs, menus, or any content requiring a structured, interactive display.

accordion.description: Enables single-panel-only expansion mode when true

activeKey.description: Specifies which panel(s) are currently expanded

defaultActiveKey.description: Sets which panel(s) start expanded on initial render

ghost.description: Removes borders/background and moves expand icons right for a minimal look

items.description: Array of panel configurations containing key, label, children and optional disabled flag

onChange.description: Fires when panels are toggled, receiving the active panel key(s)
